<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>
<head>
    <title>Wonders of Universe</title>

    <link rel="stylesheet" href="style.css">

    <style>
        body{
            background-color:#f7f6ff;
        }
    </style>

</head>

<body>

    <h1 style="color:#2d0c8c;
               font-size:60px;
               text-align:center;
               font-family:Georgia;">
        🌌 Wonders of Universe
    </h1>

    <p style="font-size:24px;
              color:#333366;
              text-align:center;">
        The universe is a vast and mysterious place filled with stars,
        planets, galaxies and cosmic wonders.
    </p>

    <h2>✨ Marvels Found in the Universe ✨</h2>

    <div class="container">

        <div class="card">
            <img src="star.jpg" alt="Star">
            <h3>⭐ Stars</h3>
            <p>
                Stars are giant glowing balls of hot gases that produce light and energy.
            </p>
        </div>

        <div class="card">
            <img src="planet.jpg" alt="Planet">
            <h3>🪐 Planets</h3>
            <p>
                Planets revolve around stars and come in different sizes and compositions.
            </p>
        </div>

        <div class="card">
            <img src="galaxy.jpg" alt="Galaxy">
            <h3>🌌 Galaxies</h3>
            <p>
                Galaxies contain billions of stars, dust and gases.
            </p>
        </div>

        <div class="card">
            <img src="comet.jpg" alt="Comet">
            <h3>☄️ Comets</h3>
            <p>
                Comets travel through space and develop glowing tails near the Sun.
            </p>
        </div>

        <div class="card">
            <img src="blackhole.jpg" alt="Black Hole">
            <h3>🕳️ Black Holes</h3>
            <p>
                Black holes have extremely strong gravity that even light cannot escape.
            </p>
        </div>

    </div>

    <div class="fact-box">
        <h2>💡 Did You Know?</h2>

        <p>
            Light from some distant galaxies takes millions of years
            to reach Earth. When we observe those galaxies, we are
            actually looking into the past.
        </p>
    </div>

    <footer>
        ✨ © 2026 Wonders of Universe | Keep Exploring the Cosmos ✨
    </footer>

</body>
</html>
